name: wheel-inspect
documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the "wheel-inspect" package available on PyPI (Python Package Index), which is a tool for extracting information from Python wheel files and *.dist-info directories, outputting it as JSON-serializable objects. The package, authored by John Thorvald Wodder II, is licensed under the MIT License and requires Python version 3.6 or higher. It is currently in a beta development status and is intended for developers. The package can be installed using pip and includes a command-line tool (`wheel2json`) for inspecting wheel files and directories. The latest version, 1.7.1, was released on April 8, 2022. The HTML also includes a warning for users with unsupported browsers (IE9 and below) and notes that some features may not work without JavaScript.
